    Don Layman Retweeted Kevin Hall

    FFA from adipose are always released in excess into blood & recycled via VLDL. FFA are essential fuels for heart & muscle. With ~50% daily kcal from Carbs & ~35% from fat, the derangement of excess kcal begins with compensatory insulin response. What evidence 4 adipose w/o Carbs?https://twitter.com/KevinH_PhD/status/1105882094503424000 …

    Don Layman added,

    Kevin Hall @KevinH_PhD
    Replying to @donlayman @BioLayne
    The relative contribution of hepatic DNL versus FFA from adipose to hepatic TG is an interesting and important topic, especially considering the likely individual variability in relative contribution. Low carb beneficial if DNL driven, but might exacerbate if adipose FFA driven?
